# Design System & Component Standards

## Stack

- React 18+ with TypeScript
- Bun as runtime and package manager
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Component-driven architecture

## Naming Conventions

- Components: PascalCase (e.g., UserCard, NavBar)
- Files: Match component names (UserCard.tsx)
- Props interfaces: ComponentNameProps
- CSS classes: Use Tailwind utilities first, custom classes as exceptions

## Component Structure

Every component should follow this pattern:

1. Import statements
2. Type definitions (interfaces)
3. Component function
4. Export statement

## Accessibility Requirements

- All interactive elements must have proper ARIA labels
- Maintain color contrast ratios of at least 4.5:1
- Support keyboard navigation
- Include semantic HTML elements

## Code Style

- Use functional components with hooks only
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- Keep components under 200 lines; split if larger
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
